The paper discusses the development of an ontology for representing quality metadata of linked datasets, which involves aspects of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) in terms of benchmarking and identifying quality problems, as well as database (cs.DB) and information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques for organising and browsing the quality metadata. The use of statistical observations and data cube visualisation tools also suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and software engineering (cs.SE) for improving the quality of data.
